               <physDesc>
                  <p> The metre of the verse is <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">mandākrāntā</foreign>.
                     Perhaps a word play on <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">bha</foreign>, “splendour”
                     and “constellation”: “in the Śrāvaṇa constellation/in the splendour of Viṣṇu,
                     that is the same as his own Sarvādvaita doctrine, Śrīnivāsa [...] copied here
                     the manuscript of the <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">ṛcas</foreign>”. </p>
               </physDesc>
            </msDesc>
